1
00:00:09,208 --> 00:00:11,000
[BATO]
I have to grab his belt!

2
00:00:12,208 --> 00:00:13,416
[YUMA]
Lower block.

3
00:00:13,500 --> 00:00:14,666
Reverse strike.

4
00:00:14,750 --> 00:00:17,000
Joint strikes.

5
00:00:17,083 --> 00:00:18,416
Inside leg trip.

6
00:00:18,500 --> 00:00:22,125
Partial Lunge
Castle Break Punch!

7
00:00:22,208 --> 00:00:24,083
There's still fire in his eyes.

8
00:00:24,166 --> 00:00:25,791
-No.
-[grunting]

9
00:00:27,750 --> 00:00:29,958
[YUMA]
Trust the team. Trust them.

10
00:00:30,041 --> 00:00:32,208
And never stop fighting.

11
00:00:32,291 --> 00:00:33,541
You can do it, Yuma.

12
00:00:33,625 --> 00:00:35,875
[YUMA] Keep hitting
till your arms fall off.

13
00:00:35,958 --> 00:00:38,333
Hear me?
Put it all on the line!

14
00:00:38,416 --> 00:00:39,625
Everything!

15
00:00:39,708 --> 00:00:40,791
[grunting]

16
00:00:40,875 --> 00:00:42,583
Keep striking, Yuma.
Take him down!

17
00:00:42,666 --> 00:00:43,708
[grunts]

18
00:00:45,666 --> 00:00:47,583
♪

19
00:00:47,666 --> 00:00:49,041
[YUMA panting]

20
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:53,583
[REFEREE]
East side wins!

21
00:00:53,666 --> 00:00:56,750
♪

22
00:00:56,833 --> 00:01:00,083
They actually did it.
They came back from the brink.

23
00:01:00,166 --> 00:01:02,041
[SADA]
That's two for Dachi.

24
00:01:02,125 --> 00:01:03,333
They're tied.

25
00:01:03,416 --> 00:01:04,750
[KANAMORI]
Which means the tournament's

26
00:01:04,833 --> 00:01:06,458
going to the fifth bout.

27
00:01:06,541 --> 00:01:09,625
[ANNOUNCER] Gojo wins by pushing
his opponent out of the ring.

28
00:01:09,708 --> 00:01:11,166
-[panting]
-[CROWD cheering]

29
00:01:13,208 --> 00:01:14,750
-[footsteps approaching]
-[gasps]

30
00:01:14,833 --> 00:01:16,541
Hail the king of the ring!

31
00:01:16,625 --> 00:01:18,000
The what?

32
00:01:18,083 --> 00:01:19,750
You just took down
a would-be national treasure!

33
00:01:19,833 --> 00:01:21,333
You're insane, dude.

34
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:24,333
You did it.

35
00:01:24,416 --> 00:01:26,125
-[chuckles softly]
-[gasps]

36
00:01:26,208 --> 00:01:27,541
♪

37
00:01:29,083 --> 00:01:30,875
[YUMA]
Today, I feel one step closer

38
00:01:30,958 --> 00:01:32,375
to earning forgiveness.

39
00:01:32,458 --> 00:01:33,458
[BOTH]
Yeah!

40
00:01:33,541 --> 00:01:34,791
[BOTH laugh]

41
00:01:35,875 --> 00:01:36,750
[laughs]

42
00:01:36,833 --> 00:01:38,666
[ALL crying]

43
00:01:40,833 --> 00:01:43,666
♪

44
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:47,583
Gojo was amazing, wasn't he?

45
00:01:47,666 --> 00:01:49,333
I wish we were down there,

46
00:01:49,416 --> 00:01:52,000
so we could celebrate with them.

47
00:01:52,083 --> 00:01:54,000
[REINA sobbing]

48
00:01:54,083 --> 00:01:56,291
[REINA]
I'm so proud of you, Yuma.

49
00:01:58,166 --> 00:02:00,708
But it's not over yet.

50
00:02:01,916 --> 00:02:05,375
Thanks to my brother
and the rest of the team,

51
00:02:05,458 --> 00:02:07,375
it's his turn.

52
00:02:07,458 --> 00:02:09,333
Hinomaru gets a second chance.

53
00:03:41,583 --> 00:03:43,208
[AUDIENCE applauding]

54
00:03:44,916 --> 00:03:45,875
-Huh?
-Huh?

55
00:03:45,958 --> 00:03:47,166
[groaning]

56
00:03:49,500 --> 00:03:51,000
Bato.

57
00:03:51,083 --> 00:03:52,625
He must be devastated.

58
00:03:52,708 --> 00:03:55,166
You could see it
when he bested Gojo in strikes.

59
00:03:55,250 --> 00:03:57,791
On paper, he was clearly
the stronger wrestler.

60
00:03:57,875 --> 00:03:59,583
This was supposed to be
an easy win.

61
00:03:59,666 --> 00:04:02,250
Stats don't determine who wins.

62
00:04:02,333 --> 00:04:04,125
When it came time,
Gojo didn't hesitate

63
00:04:04,208 --> 00:04:05,833
to use every ace
up his sleeve.

64
00:04:05,916 --> 00:04:09,125
He caught Bato off-guard
over and over again.

65
00:04:09,208 --> 00:04:11,625
And then there was
that final barrage.

66
00:04:11,708 --> 00:04:13,833
He was putting
every ounce of energy he had

67
00:04:13,916 --> 00:04:15,833
into those strikes.

68
00:04:15,916 --> 00:04:18,458
But if you want
the basic reason Bato lost,

69
00:04:18,541 --> 00:04:21,750
it's because this bout was
just a pit stop on his journey.

70
00:04:21,833 --> 00:04:24,208
But to Gojo,
it meant everything.

71
00:04:25,208 --> 00:04:26,125
I failed you, boss!

72
00:04:34,458 --> 00:04:36,125
[TENNOJI] What's with
all the doom and gloom?

73
00:04:36,208 --> 00:04:38,416
You're acting like
we've already lost the match.

74
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:42,875
If you've gotta
blame someone, blame me.

75
00:04:42,958 --> 00:04:46,041
It's my fault for losing
to Kusanagi earlier.

76
00:04:46,125 --> 00:04:48,041
[ALL gasp]

77
00:04:48,125 --> 00:04:49,625
I could tell you were worried

78
00:04:49,708 --> 00:04:52,208
about how I'd handle
being defeated.

79
00:04:52,291 --> 00:04:53,916
But after seeing
how motivated you were

80
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:57,291
to give me a second chance,
I feel reinvigorated.

81
00:04:58,625 --> 00:05:00,708
You all did great sumo
out there.

82
00:05:00,791 --> 00:05:03,666
All of us?
What bouts were you watching?

83
00:05:04,708 --> 00:05:06,416
I was a complete mess.

84
00:05:06,500 --> 00:05:08,041
I saw you fight,

85
00:05:08,125 --> 00:05:11,416
and, yeah, you may have lost,
but you made it look good.

86
00:05:11,500 --> 00:05:13,750
I've caused you
the most trouble.

87
00:05:13,833 --> 00:05:15,291
Haven't I, Aki?

88
00:05:15,375 --> 00:05:16,208
[grunts]

89
00:05:17,333 --> 00:05:19,000
[TENNOJI]
And why are you crying, Bato?

90
00:05:19,083 --> 00:05:20,041
Knock it off.

91
00:05:20,125 --> 00:05:21,875
This isn't the singles match,

92
00:05:21,958 --> 00:05:23,041
so hold your head high

93
00:05:23,125 --> 00:05:24,916
until all the bouts
are completed.

94
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:28,375
You belong to the legendary
Hakuro High sumo team.

95
00:05:28,458 --> 00:05:31,041
Losing will never change that.

96
00:05:31,125 --> 00:05:33,375
[gasps]
Sir!

97
00:05:33,458 --> 00:05:34,833
Did you hear me?

98
00:05:34,916 --> 00:05:37,250
I want all of you
to stop looking so miserable,

99
00:05:37,333 --> 00:05:40,041
and get fired up
for the fifth bout!

100
00:05:40,125 --> 00:05:41,250
[BOTH gasp]

101
00:05:41,333 --> 00:05:45,208
[ALL]
Hakuro! Hakuro! Hakuro! Hakuro!

102
00:05:45,291 --> 00:05:46,916
That's right.

103
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:49,458
They may have tied the score,
but Hakuro's captain is up next.

104
00:05:49,541 --> 00:05:51,416
Despite losing to Kusanagi,

105
00:05:51,500 --> 00:05:54,458
he's still acting
just like a yokozuna.

106
00:05:54,541 --> 00:05:56,416
There are people
that'll see his display

107
00:05:56,500 --> 00:05:58,083
and get the wrong idea.

108
00:05:58,166 --> 00:06:01,500
That it's just empty bravado
or he's got an inflated ego.

109
00:06:01,583 --> 00:06:03,375
-[CROWD] Hakuro! Hakuro!
-Let 'em.

110
00:06:03,458 --> 00:06:05,875
He understands
his responsibility.

111
00:06:05,958 --> 00:06:08,125
He's giving the crowd
what they wanna see.

112
00:06:08,208 --> 00:06:10,125
[CROWD]
Hakuro! Hakuro!

113
00:06:10,208 --> 00:06:12,625
Once he steps foot
inside the sumo ring

114
00:06:12,708 --> 00:06:15,208
nothing will stand in his way.

115
00:06:15,291 --> 00:06:18,291
And the intensity he kept
in check will be unleashed.

116
00:06:19,416 --> 00:06:20,750
[TENNOJI]
I regret how I approached

117
00:06:20,833 --> 00:06:22,583
my bout with Kusanagi.

118
00:06:22,666 --> 00:06:25,916
I went in feeling
like I was the underdog.

119
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:27,541
No matter
what anyone else says,

120
00:06:27,625 --> 00:06:30,625
I'm the greatest high school
sumo wrestler alive.

121
00:06:30,708 --> 00:06:35,125
I'm the yokozuna.
And I won't lose again.

122
00:06:35,208 --> 00:06:36,291
[ALL gasp]

123
00:06:39,208 --> 00:06:40,666
[HINOMARU]
Don't hold back.

124
00:06:40,750 --> 00:06:42,791
I came here
to defeat a yokozuna,

125
00:06:42,875 --> 00:06:44,500
and that's what
I'm going to do!

126
00:06:44,583 --> 00:06:46,791
♪

127
00:06:54,583 --> 00:06:56,416
Listen, guys, thank you.

128
00:06:57,916 --> 00:07:00,916
I'm only standing here now
because of your efforts.

129
00:07:02,500 --> 00:07:05,000
No, not just my team's.

130
00:07:05,083 --> 00:07:07,208
There are so many people
who helped me.

131
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:10,750
I'm indebted to them.

132
00:07:10,833 --> 00:07:13,250
-In that case, you better win.
-Agreed.

133
00:07:13,333 --> 00:07:15,166
Losing's not an option.

134
00:07:15,250 --> 00:07:17,500
Ushio! Win this!

135
00:07:17,583 --> 00:07:18,708
Yeah!

136
00:07:19,708 --> 00:07:21,333
Someone who wants
to be a yokozuna

137
00:07:21,416 --> 00:07:23,541
can't afford to lose twice.

138
00:07:23,625 --> 00:07:25,250
But above all,

139
00:07:25,333 --> 00:07:27,666
they worked hard
to give me a second chance,

140
00:07:27,750 --> 00:07:30,583
and I'm not about to waste it!

141
00:07:30,666 --> 00:07:32,041
[ANNOUNCER]
Fifth bout.

142
00:07:32,125 --> 00:07:36,416
On the east side, Ushio.
On the west side, Tennoji.

143
00:07:36,500 --> 00:07:39,458
Hinomaru lost to him
only a couple of days ago.

144
00:07:39,541 --> 00:07:42,875
Could anything have drastically
changed in that amount of time?

145
00:07:43,875 --> 00:07:45,750
You should know.

146
00:07:45,833 --> 00:07:48,041
Sumo wrestlers
live in the moment,

147
00:07:48,125 --> 00:07:50,708
and all they need
is a moment to transform.

148
00:07:51,791 --> 00:07:53,083
[HINOMARU]
I can tell,

149
00:07:53,166 --> 00:07:55,166
you're different
from the last time we fought.

150
00:07:55,250 --> 00:07:56,791
[REFEREE]
Hands on the ground.

151
00:07:58,708 --> 00:08:01,000
[HINOMARU] Which means
I'll have to transform myself!

152
00:08:01,083 --> 00:08:02,458
That's way low.

153
00:08:02,541 --> 00:08:04,416
He's almost at ground level.

154
00:08:05,625 --> 00:08:07,541
[TENNOJI]
We're in the same boat here.

155
00:08:07,625 --> 00:08:10,000
Each of us lost
an important bout.

156
00:08:10,083 --> 00:08:13,416
Which is why I can't
take this one lightly.

157
00:08:13,500 --> 00:08:16,375
I know your body is also
surging with this power.

158
00:08:16,458 --> 00:08:18,875
The will to make a comeback.

159
00:08:18,958 --> 00:08:19,958
[SAKI groans softly]

160
00:08:21,458 --> 00:08:23,041
[shudders]

161
00:08:26,750 --> 00:08:28,875
♪

162
00:08:39,125 --> 00:08:41,083
[REFEREE]
Spirit!

163
00:08:41,166 --> 00:08:43,125
[HINOMARU]
A forearm charge? Not this time!

164
00:08:43,208 --> 00:08:44,125
-[gasps]
-Got it!

165
00:08:44,208 --> 00:08:45,500
[HINOMARU]
Right arm lock?

166
00:08:45,583 --> 00:08:47,000
Don't think so!

167
00:08:47,083 --> 00:08:48,833
No stopping! Press forward!

168
00:08:48,916 --> 00:08:50,791
Demon Wheel!

169
00:08:51,833 --> 00:08:53,333
He knew.

170
00:08:53,416 --> 00:08:54,458
[grunts]

171
00:08:54,541 --> 00:08:55,750
[TENNOJI]
Left arm latch-on.

172
00:08:55,833 --> 00:08:57,625
[REINA]
He's trapped!

173
00:08:57,708 --> 00:08:59,583
[SAKI gasps]
He let go of his belt!

174
00:08:59,666 --> 00:09:01,083
[HINOMARU]
Arm throw!

175
00:09:01,166 --> 00:09:03,583
[TENNOJI] You think I didn't
research that move too?

176
00:09:03,666 --> 00:09:05,375
Arm-lock twist down!

177
00:09:05,458 --> 00:09:08,708
[HINOMARU] Well, do you know
about this one?!

178
00:09:08,791 --> 00:09:10,583
Damn. They're fast.

179
00:09:10,666 --> 00:09:12,083
Of course.

180
00:09:12,166 --> 00:09:14,666
They understand more
about who they're facing now.

181
00:09:14,750 --> 00:09:16,166
[HINOMARU]
Try this on for size!

182
00:09:16,250 --> 00:09:17,833
Hinomaru idolized him

183
00:09:17,916 --> 00:09:20,625
and crafted his style
of sumo after his.

184
00:09:20,708 --> 00:09:22,125
[TENNOJI]
Show me something new.

185
00:09:22,208 --> 00:09:24,000
Nothing gets past Tennoji.

186
00:09:24,083 --> 00:09:27,291
He disarms his opponents
of every weapon they've got.

187
00:09:27,375 --> 00:09:29,875
They're familiar with
each other's special moves.

188
00:09:29,958 --> 00:09:32,875
Constantly reading
what the other's about to do

189
00:09:32,958 --> 00:09:34,916
and canceling out the strategy.

190
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:37,916
At the rate's it's going,
it's obvious who'll win.

191
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:38,916
[laughs]

192
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:39,958
[gasps]

193
00:09:43,125 --> 00:09:45,875
[SHIBAKIYAMA] He keeps getting
pushed further and further back.

194
00:09:45,958 --> 00:09:48,000
When you factor in
the number of battles

195
00:09:48,083 --> 00:09:50,083
each has fought
at the top level

196
00:09:50,166 --> 00:09:51,500
and experience,

197
00:09:51,583 --> 00:09:54,166
Hinomaru will be the first
to run out of moves.

198
00:09:55,708 --> 00:09:57,041
Hang in there, kid.

199
00:09:58,125 --> 00:09:59,375
[HINOMARU]
He's incredible.

200
00:09:59,458 --> 00:10:01,083
I'm being eaten alive.

201
00:10:01,166 --> 00:10:03,541
So this is the beast
Sosuke awakened.

202
00:10:03,625 --> 00:10:05,625
Tennoji's true form.

203
00:10:05,708 --> 00:10:06,791
[SHUNKAI]
Behold the shadow

204
00:10:06,875 --> 00:10:08,916
that blots out
an opponent's light.

205
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:11,041
This is the dark carnage
of battle.

206
00:10:13,875 --> 00:10:15,500
Hinomaru!

207
00:10:16,708 --> 00:10:18,041
[HINOMARU]
Tennoji can even anticipate

208
00:10:18,125 --> 00:10:19,625
his opponent's growth,

209
00:10:19,708 --> 00:10:21,416
and then counter it.

210
00:10:21,500 --> 00:10:25,000
If that's the case,
I've got one option.

211
00:10:25,083 --> 00:10:28,000
I need to outperform
his expectations!

212
00:10:33,791 --> 00:10:35,458
[TENNOJI]
What is this?

213
00:10:35,541 --> 00:10:39,333
Your intensity, it's gone.

214
00:10:39,416 --> 00:10:40,791
[REINA]
He's getting pummeled.

215
00:10:40,875 --> 00:10:42,416
-Yeah!
-Go!

216
00:10:42,500 --> 00:10:44,916
[SAKI] Ushio almost always
goes for an all-out offensive.

217
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:47,083
This isn't like him.

218
00:10:47,166 --> 00:10:50,083
My brother's already countered
every one of his moves.

219
00:10:50,166 --> 00:10:53,000
There's only a single way
he can win.

220
00:10:53,083 --> 00:10:55,250
Grab his belt,
knock him off balance,

221
00:10:55,333 --> 00:10:58,291
then use the Hundred-Thousand
Demon Takedown.

222
00:10:58,375 --> 00:11:00,458
But the mawashi
is too low for him.

223
00:11:00,541 --> 00:11:02,333
He can't reach it.

224
00:11:02,416 --> 00:11:05,916
Then there's the low strike
Tennoji used against Kusanagi.

225
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:07,416
Good luck bypassing it

226
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:09,458
and getting close enough
to grab on with both hands.

227
00:11:09,541 --> 00:11:12,583
[TENMA] The greatest weapon
you have is about to be stolen.

228
00:11:12,666 --> 00:11:14,208
What now?

229
00:11:14,291 --> 00:11:15,875
Will you let it swallow you up?

230
00:11:15,958 --> 00:11:17,125
The darkness?

231
00:11:20,125 --> 00:11:21,041
[TENNOJI]
No way.

232
00:11:21,125 --> 00:11:22,041
[TENMA gasps]

233
00:11:22,125 --> 00:11:23,333
Hey.

234
00:11:24,458 --> 00:11:26,500
Why'd he pull back?

235
00:11:26,583 --> 00:11:29,916
[TENNOJI] That was
a grave mistake, Hinomaru.

236
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:32,291
You just acknowledged
this is as far as you can go

237
00:11:32,375 --> 00:11:34,625
fighting me head-on
with your physique.

238
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:38,333
The reason you made it here

239
00:11:38,416 --> 00:11:40,541
is because
you never accepted that before.

240
00:11:40,625 --> 00:11:43,083
You retreated like a coward.

241
00:11:43,166 --> 00:11:45,250
It's unacceptable!

242
00:11:45,333 --> 00:11:47,958
[KARIYA] Was Tennoji's intensity
too much for you?

243
00:11:48,041 --> 00:11:49,666
You were supposed
to show me the path

244
00:11:49,750 --> 00:11:52,458
I didn't have
the courage to take.

245
00:11:52,541 --> 00:11:55,208
Why would you run away now?!

246
00:11:55,291 --> 00:11:57,833
No. He isn't.

247
00:11:59,625 --> 00:12:02,250
His heart's
still in the fight.

248
00:12:02,333 --> 00:12:04,958
Hinomaru hasn't stopped
moving forward.

249
00:12:05,041 --> 00:12:07,791
He only stepped back so he could
take a more powerful leap.

250
00:12:09,708 --> 00:12:12,458
[HINOMARU]
I lost because I was weak.

251
00:12:12,541 --> 00:12:14,541
I used my strength

252
00:12:14,625 --> 00:12:16,541
but didn't realize
that wasn't enough.

253
00:12:18,500 --> 00:12:20,666
Defeat taught me
something valuable.

254
00:12:20,750 --> 00:12:23,916
That I didn't get to be
where I am by myself!

255
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:24,916
[gasps]

256
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:26,500
[REINA]
Isn't that...

257
00:12:26,583 --> 00:12:28,166
[HINOMARU]
There's Yuma, raining strikes

258
00:12:28,250 --> 00:12:30,208
on me every practice.

259
00:12:30,291 --> 00:12:31,791
And, man, do they hurt!

260
00:12:31,875 --> 00:12:33,291
A lunge punch?

261
00:12:33,375 --> 00:12:35,125
[TENNOJI]
What was that?

262
00:12:35,208 --> 00:12:36,166
A leap.

263
00:12:38,375 --> 00:12:40,500
No. He bluffed.

264
00:12:40,583 --> 00:12:43,500
[HINOMARU]
Then there's your reverse, Kei.

265
00:12:43,583 --> 00:12:47,000
It nearly fools me every time,
even when I'm expecting it.

266
00:12:47,083 --> 00:12:48,583
[SHIBAKIYAMA]
He's always practiced

267
00:12:48,666 --> 00:12:50,125
varying up his attacks.

268
00:12:50,208 --> 00:12:52,875
Mixing strong and weak moves.

269
00:12:52,958 --> 00:12:54,875
But never like this.

270
00:12:54,958 --> 00:12:58,291
Pulling back gave him more room
to launch an attack.

271
00:12:58,375 --> 00:12:59,458
[grunts]

272
00:12:59,541 --> 00:13:00,583
[SHIBAKIYAMA]
His head-on approach

273
00:13:00,666 --> 00:13:02,291
is shining brighter than ever.

274
00:13:02,375 --> 00:13:05,000
[SAKI] With such a wide variety
of attacks,

275
00:13:05,083 --> 00:13:07,541
my brother can't predict
what'll come next.

276
00:13:08,583 --> 00:13:11,916
[SHUNKAI] To him, his sumo
represents a way of life.

277
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:14,791
If he thought at any time
retreating was the answer,

278
00:13:14,875 --> 00:13:16,875
the flame inside of him
would extinguish.

279
00:13:16,958 --> 00:13:18,833
Sumo.

280
00:13:18,916 --> 00:13:20,875
His way of life.

281
00:13:20,958 --> 00:13:22,875
And his resolve.

282
00:13:22,958 --> 00:13:26,291
Each one contributes
to the fire in his eye.

283
00:13:27,708 --> 00:13:30,166
That demonic,
enduring determination!

284
00:13:31,708 --> 00:13:32,583
[HINOMARU grunts]

285
00:13:32,666 --> 00:13:34,625
Hundred-Thousand Demon Drop!

286
00:13:34,708 --> 00:13:36,583
♪

287
00:13:38,333 --> 00:13:40,166
[HINOMARU] I used to think
being fifth on the roster

288
00:13:40,250 --> 00:13:42,958
meant never showing weakness
in front of my teammates.

289
00:13:44,625 --> 00:13:47,208
That I needed to be strong
all the time.

290
00:13:47,291 --> 00:13:50,958
To assume the role of leader,
because I was best suited.

291
00:13:51,041 --> 00:13:52,958
And if I ever stopped
moving forward,

292
00:13:53,041 --> 00:13:55,291
they wouldn't be able
to continue either.

293
00:13:55,375 --> 00:13:57,208
That's what I thought.

294
00:13:57,291 --> 00:13:59,166
And I was so wrong.

295
00:13:59,250 --> 00:14:02,041
After I lost,
I could see it clearly.

296
00:14:02,125 --> 00:14:05,625
My teammates marching forward,
steady and strong.

297
00:14:06,750 --> 00:14:08,666
If you think
that's all I've got,

298
00:14:08,750 --> 00:14:10,916
you haven't seen anything yet!

299
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:14,583
My body has the sumo
of my entire team inside of it.

300
00:14:14,666 --> 00:14:16,458
Like Chihiro's freestyle!

301
00:14:16,541 --> 00:14:17,750
[chuckles]

302
00:14:19,083 --> 00:14:20,833
Backward hook body drop!

303
00:14:20,916 --> 00:14:22,500
A falling technique!

304
00:14:22,583 --> 00:14:24,875
[SHUNKAI] Throwing and pushing
side-to-side,

305
00:14:24,958 --> 00:14:27,375
followed by a pullback and fall.

306
00:14:27,458 --> 00:14:30,125
Even Tennoji couldn't
anticipate that.

307
00:14:30,208 --> 00:14:31,625
Take him down!

308
00:14:31,708 --> 00:14:33,375
Don't quit now!

309
00:14:34,708 --> 00:14:36,541
[grunts]

310
00:14:36,625 --> 00:14:37,750
[HINOMARU gasps]

311
00:14:37,833 --> 00:14:39,833
Do you know why
out of all the schools

312
00:14:39,916 --> 00:14:41,541
I chose Tottori Hakuro?

313
00:14:41,625 --> 00:14:44,041
Every day I get
to face specialists

314
00:14:44,125 --> 00:14:46,166
with a wide array of techniques,

315
00:14:46,250 --> 00:14:47,625
which means I'm ready
for anything

316
00:14:47,708 --> 00:14:49,625
an opponent can throw at me.

317
00:14:49,708 --> 00:14:51,541
You're not the only person
who's stronger

318
00:14:51,625 --> 00:14:53,291
because of his teammates.

319
00:14:53,375 --> 00:14:55,000
[grunts]

320
00:14:55,083 --> 00:14:58,000
[TENNOJI] So try outperforming
my expectations all you'd like.

321
00:14:58,083 --> 00:15:00,416
It'll end the same way
every time.

322
00:15:00,500 --> 00:15:02,416
Nobody compares to me!

323
00:15:02,500 --> 00:15:05,916
My team has made me
the best sumo wrestler around!

324
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:06,958
[grunting]

325
00:15:10,500 --> 00:15:12,250
[HINOMARU] You noticed something
about our first bout?

326
00:15:12,333 --> 00:15:15,708
Yeah. I'm not certain
how useful it'll be,

327
00:15:15,791 --> 00:15:17,291
but I compared it
to your other matches

328
00:15:17,375 --> 00:15:18,500
and it stood out.

329
00:15:18,583 --> 00:15:19,708
Take a look.

330
00:15:19,791 --> 00:15:21,375
Right there.

331
00:15:21,458 --> 00:15:23,166
[HINOMARU]
Can't get overwhelmed.

332
00:15:23,250 --> 00:15:24,791
Keep on attacking.

333
00:15:24,875 --> 00:15:27,166
Reverse Hundred Demon Takedown!

334
00:15:28,208 --> 00:15:30,541
Keep it up.
Knock him off balance.

335
00:15:30,625 --> 00:15:32,583
Don't stop till you win.

336
00:15:32,666 --> 00:15:34,833
Hundred-Thousand Demon Takedown!

337
00:15:36,041 --> 00:15:38,208
You did the Hundred-Thousand
Demon Drop,

338
00:15:38,291 --> 00:15:42,000
after the push, which ended up
weakening the centrifugal force.

339
00:15:42,083 --> 00:15:45,416
Meaning this move wasn't
executed at full-strength.

340
00:15:45,500 --> 00:15:48,916
Basically, the more you're able
to shake him side-to-side--

341
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:51,083
It has more power.

342
00:15:51,166 --> 00:15:52,125
Keep going.

343
00:15:52,208 --> 00:15:54,291
Make Tennoji lose his footing!

344
00:15:54,375 --> 00:15:57,583
Swirl around him
like an inferno!

345
00:15:57,666 --> 00:16:00,416
Reverse Hundred-Thousand
Demon Drop!

346
00:16:00,500 --> 00:16:02,041
♪

347
00:16:02,125 --> 00:16:03,250
[REINA sighs]

348
00:16:03,333 --> 00:16:05,875
Hori's something else.
What a manager.

349
00:16:05,958 --> 00:16:07,041
What?

350
00:16:07,125 --> 00:16:08,166
Technically we have
the same role,

351
00:16:08,250 --> 00:16:09,333
but she always finds a way

352
00:16:09,416 --> 00:16:11,208
to help you guys
be more successful.

353
00:16:11,291 --> 00:16:13,083
I'm completely useless.

354
00:16:14,416 --> 00:16:16,083
[HINOMARU chuckles]

355
00:16:16,166 --> 00:16:17,583
[HINOMARU]
You're wrong about that.

356
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:20,833
[REINA]
What?

357
00:16:20,916 --> 00:16:21,875
[gasps]

358
00:16:21,958 --> 00:16:24,416
[TENNOJI grunting]

359
00:16:26,916 --> 00:16:29,041
[HINOMARU]
See this technique?

360
00:16:29,125 --> 00:16:30,666
Kirihito.

361
00:16:30,750 --> 00:16:32,541
The Shibakiyama Stable guys.

362
00:16:32,625 --> 00:16:35,208
The Masters, both of them.

363
00:16:36,541 --> 00:16:37,625
My rivals.

364
00:16:38,958 --> 00:16:40,125
My team.

365
00:16:40,208 --> 00:16:42,625
You got this! Yeah!

366
00:16:42,708 --> 00:16:45,416
[HINOMARU] And you, Reina.
You all helped me complete it.

367
00:16:46,583 --> 00:16:49,541
Tennoji, you're godlike.

368
00:16:49,625 --> 00:16:52,125
And I never could've
defeated you alone.

369
00:16:52,208 --> 00:16:55,250
But we're not alone anymore.

370
00:16:55,333 --> 00:16:56,750
Are we, Captain?

371
00:16:58,291 --> 00:17:01,458
Let him have it, Ushio!

372
00:17:01,541 --> 00:17:03,958
[HINOMARU]
Here's goes everything I've got!

373
00:17:04,041 --> 00:17:06,166
Demon's Enduring Determination!

374
00:17:06,250 --> 00:17:09,208
Hundred-Thousand Demon Drop!

375
00:17:09,291 --> 00:17:11,208
Go!

376
00:17:11,291 --> 00:17:13,458
Drop him!

377
00:17:13,541 --> 00:17:15,333
[groans sharply]

378
00:17:15,416 --> 00:17:16,416
[HINOMARU]
Something's wrong!

379
00:17:17,750 --> 00:17:19,208
[TENNOJI grunts]

380
00:17:20,375 --> 00:17:22,958
[HINOMARU] Even now,
with everything on the line,

381
00:17:23,041 --> 00:17:24,583
you're smiling.

382
00:17:24,666 --> 00:17:26,625
[TENNOJI]
Kusanagi already beat me.

383
00:17:26,708 --> 00:17:29,500
Which means I'm no longer
a champion.

384
00:17:29,583 --> 00:17:31,041
But still,

385
00:17:31,125 --> 00:17:34,000
I am the captain of the greatest
high school sumo team.

386
00:17:34,083 --> 00:17:36,500
I can't afford to be weak.

387
00:17:36,583 --> 00:17:38,666
You won't stop me from smiling,

388
00:17:38,750 --> 00:17:40,500
even when
I'm on the brink of death.

389
00:17:40,583 --> 00:17:44,000
I'm taking my team to the top
no matter the price!

390
00:17:44,083 --> 00:17:46,291
[SHUNKAI] He still had
enough strength to use a throw.

391
00:17:46,375 --> 00:17:48,291
[SHIBAKIYAMA]
What sheer grit.

392
00:17:48,375 --> 00:17:50,625
[groaning]

393
00:17:50,708 --> 00:17:52,166
[HINOMARU]
Just as expected.

394
00:17:52,250 --> 00:17:53,291
You're incredible.

395
00:17:53,375 --> 00:17:55,041
[CHIZUKO]
His left arm's locked.

396
00:17:55,125 --> 00:17:56,375
[KEI]
Is this it?

397
00:17:56,458 --> 00:17:58,291
[REINA] Even if you've
reached your limit,

398
00:17:58,375 --> 00:18:01,291
you still have
your greatest weapon.

399
00:18:01,375 --> 00:18:03,541
Your determination.

400
00:18:03,625 --> 00:18:06,291
It may look bad.
Doesn't matter.

401
00:18:06,375 --> 00:18:08,250
You never bend!

402
00:18:08,333 --> 00:18:10,375
That's your style of fighting.

403
00:18:10,458 --> 00:18:12,541
Your Hinomaru Sumo!

404
00:18:12,625 --> 00:18:14,416
[grunts]

405
00:18:15,458 --> 00:18:17,125
[HINOMARU]
I'm glad I idolized you.

406
00:18:17,208 --> 00:18:20,083
The reason I came this far
wasn't just my team.

407
00:18:20,166 --> 00:18:21,375
There was something else.

408
00:18:21,458 --> 00:18:23,500
I've been chasing
after a colossus,

409
00:18:23,583 --> 00:18:26,583
and his name
is Shido Tennoji.

410
00:18:26,666 --> 00:18:29,000
I don't know
if I've conquered that mountain.

411
00:18:29,083 --> 00:18:32,333
It's very possible
you're still stronger than me.

412
00:18:32,416 --> 00:18:35,000
But I'm okay with that.

413
00:18:36,625 --> 00:18:39,041
Everyone got me here today.

414
00:18:39,125 --> 00:18:43,041
This is it.
I have to come out victorious!

415
00:18:43,125 --> 00:18:44,875
Even if it kills me!

416
00:18:57,375 --> 00:18:58,541
[gasps]

417
00:19:06,041 --> 00:19:08,958
[ALL cheering]

418
00:19:09,041 --> 00:19:11,791
♪

419
00:19:11,875 --> 00:19:13,166
[grunts]

420
00:19:14,875 --> 00:19:19,916
[yelling]
Yeah!

421
00:19:22,333 --> 00:19:23,833
[gasping]

422
00:19:26,208 --> 00:19:28,291
[SHUNKAI] It's considered
bad form to shout

423
00:19:28,375 --> 00:19:30,625
or do a victory pose
in the ring.

424
00:19:30,708 --> 00:19:35,000
But this time,
an exception can be made.

425
00:19:35,083 --> 00:19:37,041
This wasn't just any victory.

426
00:19:38,333 --> 00:19:40,250
Not by a long shot.

427
00:19:41,291 --> 00:19:43,333
[ANNOUNCER]
Odachi on the east side wins.

428
00:19:43,416 --> 00:19:45,000
Three-two.

429
00:19:45,083 --> 00:19:47,625
Did Dachi High really
just make it to the final round

430
00:19:47,708 --> 00:19:49,958
in their first
national tournament?

431
00:19:50,041 --> 00:19:53,250
They beat Tennoji
and took down the Hakuro team.

432
00:19:53,333 --> 00:19:55,708
[TENNOJI panting]

433
00:19:56,875 --> 00:19:58,666
[gasps]

434
00:19:58,750 --> 00:20:00,291
Good work out there.

435
00:20:00,375 --> 00:20:01,750
Let's go.

436
00:20:01,833 --> 00:20:03,750
The third place spot's
calling our name.

437
00:20:04,750 --> 00:20:06,458
Hmm.

438
00:20:06,541 --> 00:20:08,208
Do me a favor, you idiots.

439
00:20:08,291 --> 00:20:10,958
Don't put on a brave face.

440
00:20:11,041 --> 00:20:12,250
Not for my sake.

441
00:20:12,333 --> 00:20:14,875
When you're disappointed,
show it.

442
00:20:14,958 --> 00:20:16,708
Etch it into your heart.

443
00:20:16,791 --> 00:20:21,958
Because one day, that feeling
will become your strength.

444
00:20:22,041 --> 00:20:24,875
[AUDIENCE applauding]

445
00:20:26,541 --> 00:20:29,166
[TENNOJI]
I let you down, too.

446
00:20:29,250 --> 00:20:32,958
I couldn't make you the manager
of the best team in Japan.

447
00:20:33,041 --> 00:20:34,958
Stop worrying about me.

448
00:20:35,041 --> 00:20:36,625
For once in your life,
try to focus

449
00:20:36,708 --> 00:20:38,875
on your own feelings
for a change.

450
00:20:38,958 --> 00:20:40,916
[TENNOJI]
My own feelings, huh?

451
00:20:42,666 --> 00:20:45,208
Hinomaru struck a victory pose.

452
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:51,375
But that's fine.
After all, you beat me.

453
00:20:51,458 --> 00:20:54,500
I'd be disappointed
if you didn't show any emotion.

454
00:20:54,583 --> 00:20:57,708
The score is now one-all.

455
00:20:57,791 --> 00:21:00,333
We'll have our decider
in the pro league.

456
00:21:00,416 --> 00:21:02,250
You better win.

457
00:21:02,333 --> 00:21:05,208
A lot of people
are rooting for you.

458
00:21:05,291 --> 00:21:06,625
Don't let them down.

459
00:21:09,875 --> 00:21:11,875
♪

460
00:21:11,958 --> 00:21:13,833
[YOMODA sighs]
The crowd's still energized

461
00:21:13,916 --> 00:21:15,500
over that last bout.

462
00:21:15,583 --> 00:21:17,250
Hakuro High losing.

463
00:21:17,333 --> 00:21:19,375
I mean, who could've
ever predicted that?

464
00:21:19,458 --> 00:21:21,458
[laughs]
Doesn't matter.

465
00:21:21,541 --> 00:21:23,041
It's over, move on.

466
00:21:23,125 --> 00:21:25,375
If they want more,
then we'll happily give them

467
00:21:25,458 --> 00:21:28,250
a battle the likes of which
they've never seen.

468
00:21:28,333 --> 00:21:31,000
So without further delay,
gentlemen,

469
00:21:31,083 --> 00:21:33,708
how about we show 'em
what the cream of Eiga High

470
00:21:33,791 --> 00:21:35,291
has to offer up?

471
00:21:35,375 --> 00:21:38,416
♪

472
00:23:16,458 --> 00:23:17,875
♪

473
00:23:19,041 --> 00:23:20,416
See that?

474
00:23:20,500 --> 00:23:23,041
Even when he's outside the ring,
he's intimidating.

475
00:23:23,125 --> 00:23:25,125
That's because he doesn't
have any eyebrows.

476
00:23:25,208 --> 00:23:27,833
-Says who?
-[REINA and CHIZUKO gasp]

477
00:23:27,916 --> 00:23:29,750
Watch this. Ta-da.

478
00:23:29,833 --> 00:23:30,875
-Uh...
-Uh...

479
00:23:30,958 --> 00:23:32,750
They've been here
the whole time.

480
00:23:32,833 --> 00:23:33,791
Well?

481
00:23:36,125 --> 00:23:37,375
Yeah. Neat.

